As discussed [here][1], one way to get the desired axis markings is to add a [`SymbolAxis`][2] on the right, as illustrated [here][3] and below.  In addition,

- The axis/plot overlap may reflect the use of `RectangleInsets` in `setAxisOffset()`, omitted below; a third domain marker is shown instead.

- Tick mark position support is provided by [`DataAxis`][4] and `DateTickMarkPosition`.

- Instead of padding titles with spaces, use `setPadding()`, seen [here][5] and below.

- Adjust the chart&#39;s overall size as shown [here][6].

- In a Swing context, construct and manipulate GUI objects _only_ on the *[event dispatch thread][7]*.

